193&ndash;213.</li>

<li>Kraft, A., and I. Perczel, 2018, &ldquo;John Italos on the
eternity of the world&rdquo;, <em>Byzantinische Zeitschrift</em>,
111/3: 659&ndash;720.</li>

<li>Krausm&uuml;ller, D., 2015, &ldquo;What is mortal in the
soul?&rdquo;, <em>Mukaddime</em>, 6/1: 1&ndash;17.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Between Tritheism and
Sabellianism: trinitarian speculation in John Italos&rsquo; and
Nicetas Stethatos&rsquo; confessions of faith&rdquo;,
<em>Scrinium</em>, 12: 261&ndash;280.</li>

<li>Lauritzen, F., 2007, &ldquo;The debate on faith and reason&rdquo;,
<em>Jahrbuch der &Ouml;sterreichischen</em> <em>Byzantinistik</em>,
57: 75&ndash;82.</li>

<li>Magdalino, P., 1996, <em>The Byzantine background to the First
Crusade</em>, Toronto: Canadian Institute of Balkan Studies.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &ldquo;Deux philosophes italiens face
&agrave; la x&eacute;nophobie byzantine: r&eacute;p&eacute;tition ou
&eacute;volution d&rsquo;un sch&eacute;ma?&rdquo;, <em>Cahiers
d&rsquo;&eacute;tudes italiennes</em>, 25: 1&ndash;14.
 [<a href="http://cei.revues.org/3561" target="other">Magdalino 2017 available online</a>]</li>
 
<li>Mariev, S., and M. Monica, 2017, &ldquo;The divine body of the
heavens. The debates about the body of the heavens during Late
Antiquity and their echoes in the works of Michael Psellos and John
Italos&rdquo;, in <em>Byzantine Perspectives on Neoplatonism</em>, S.
Mariev (ed.), Berlin: De Gruyter, 31&ndash;65.</li>

<li>Masai, F., 1956, <em>Pl&eacute;thon et le platonisme de Mistra.
Les classiques de l&rsquo;humanisme</em>, Paris: Les Belles
Lettres.</li>

<li>Niarchos, C. G., 1996, <em>&Eta;</em>
<em>&epsilon;&lambda;&lambda;&eta;&nu;&iota;&kappa;&#942;
&phi;&iota;&lambda;&omicron;&sigma;&omicron;&phi;&#943;&alpha;
&kappa;&alpha;&tau;&#940; &tau;&eta;
&beta;&upsilon;&zeta;&alpha;&nu;&tau;&iota;&nu;&#942;&nu;
&tau;&eta;&sigmaf;
&pi;&epsilon;&rho;&#943;&omicron;&delta;&omicron;&nu;</em>, Athens:
&#7960;&kappa;&delta;&#972;&sigma;&epsilon;&iota;&sigmaf;
&tau;&omicron;&#8166;
&Pi;&alpha;&nu;&epsilon;&pi;&iota;&sigma;&tau;&eta;&mu;&#943;&omicron;&upsilon;
&#7944;&theta;&eta;&nu;&#8182;&nu;.</li>

<li>Nicolaidis, E., 2011, <em>Science and Eastern Orthodoxy: from the
Greek fathers to the age of globalization</em>, S. Emanuel (tr.),
Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press.</li>

<li>Nikolaou, T., 2012, &ldquo;<em>Eine quellenkritische
Untersuchung</em> des Traktats (87) De iconis der Quaestiones
Quodlibetales und seine Bedeutung hinsichtlich der Verurteilung von
Johannes Italos&rdquo;, in idem, <em>Glaube und Forsche.
Ausgew&auml;hlte Studien zur griechischen Patristik und byzantinischen
Geistesgeschichte</em>, St. Ottilien: EOS-Verlag, 375&ndash;392.</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Meara, D. J., 2021, &ldquo;Aristotelian and Neoplatonic
ethics in Michael Psellos sand John Italos&rdquo;, <em>Studia
Universitatis Babes-Bolyai Theologia Orthodoxa</em>, 66/1:
135&ndash;146.</li>

<li>Pontikos, I., 1992, &ldquo;&Eta;
&alpha;&nu;&alpha;&beta;&#943;&omega;&sigma;&eta;
&tau;&omicron;&upsilon;
&phi;&upsilon;&sigma;&iota;&kappa;&omicron;&#973;
&Alpha;&rho;&iota;&sigma;&tau;&omicron;&tau;&#941;&lambda;&eta;
&tau;&omicron;&nu; 11<sup>&omicron;</sup>
&alpha;&iota;&#974;&nu;&alpha; &sigma;&tau;&omicron;
&Beta;&upsilon;&zeta;&#940;&nu;&tau;&iota;&omicron;&rdquo;,
<em>&Delta;&omega;&delta;&#974;&nu;&eta;</em>, 21/3: 83&ndash;99.</li>

<li>Rigo, A., 2001, &ldquo;Giovanni Italo&rdquo;, in <em>Dizionario
Biografico degli Italiani</em>, <em>Vol. 56</em>, Rome: Istituto
dell&rsquo;Enciclopedia Italiana, 62&ndash;67.</li>

<li>Romano, R., 1988, &ldquo;Per la fortuna di Giovanni Italo
nell&rsquo;Italia meridionale&rdquo;,
<em>&Iota;&tau;&alpha;&lambda;&omicron;&epsilon;&lambda;&lambda;&eta;&nu;&iota;&kappa;&#940;</em>,
1: 131&ndash;138.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1994, &ldquo;Nuove testimonianze sul
Traghelaphos in Giovanni Italo&rdquo;, in
<em>&Sigma;&#973;&nu;&delta;&epsilon;&sigma;&mu;&omicron;&sigmaf;.
Studi in onore di Rosario Anastasi, Vol. 2</em>, Catania:
Universit&agrave; di Catania, 339&ndash;342.</li>

<li>Shchukin, T., 2008, &ldquo;Iconoclastic fragment of the apologetic
note by John Italos&rdquo;, <em>Scrinium</em>, 4: 249&ndash;259.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010,
&ldquo;&#1069;&#1089;&#1093;&#1072;&#1090;&#1086;&#1083;&#1086;&#1075;&#1080;&#1103;
&#1048;&#1086;&#1072;&#1085;&#1085;&#1072;
&#1048;&#1090;&#1072;&#1083;&#1072;&rdquo; [The eschatology of John
Italos], <em>&#1042;&#1077;&#1089;&#1090;&#1085;&#1080;&#1082;</em>
<em>&#1088;&#1091;&#1089;&#1089;&#1082;&#1086;&#1081;</em>
<em>&#1093;&#1088;&#1080;&#1089;&#1090;&#1080;&#1072;&#1085;&#1089;&#1082;&#1086;&#1081;
&#1075;&#1091;&#1084;&#1072;&#1085;&#1080;&#1090;&#1072;&#1088;&#1085;&#1086;&#1081;</em>
<em>&#1072;&#1082;&#1072;&#1076;&#1077;&#1084;&#1080;&#1080;</em>,
11/4: 116&ndash;120.</li>

<li>Siniossoglou, N., 2011, <em>Radical Platonism in Byzantium:
illumination and utopia in Gemistos Plethon</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press.</li>

<li>St&eacute;phanou, P. &Eacute;., 1933, &ldquo;Jean Italos:
l&rsquo;immortalit&eacute; de l&rsquo;&acirc;me et la
resurrection&rdquo;, <em>&Eacute;chos d&rsquo;Orient</em>, 32:
413&ndash;428.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1949, <em>Jean Italos: philosophe et
humaniste</em>, Rome: Pont. Institutum Orientalium Studiorum.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1957, &ldquo;Review of P. Joannou&rsquo;
Quaestiones Quodlibetales &amp; Die Illuminationslehre&rdquo;,
<em>Orientalia christiana periodica</em>, 23: 431&ndash;436.</li>

<li>Tatakis, B., 1949, <em>La philosophie Byzantine</em>, Paris.</li>

<li>Trizio, M., 2013, &ldquo;Escaping through the Homeric gates: John
Italos&rsquo; Neoplatonic exegesis of Odyssey 19.562&ndash;567:
between Synesius and Proclus&rdquo;, <em>Documenti e studi sulla
tradizione filosofica medievale</em>, 24: 69&ndash;83.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014, &ldquo;A late antique debate on
matter-evil revisited in 11th-century Byzantium: John Italos and his
Quaestio 92&rdquo;, in <em>Fate, providence and moral responsibility
in ancient, medieval and early modern thought. Studies in honour of
Carlos Steel</em>, P. d&rsquo;Hoine and G. Van Riel (eds), Leuven:
Leuven University Press, 383&ndash;394.</li>

<li>Uspenskiy, &#7710;., 1893,
<em>&#1057;&#1080;&#1085;&#1086;&#1076;&#1080;&#1082;&#1098;
&#1074;&#1098; &#1053;&#1077;&#1076;&#1123;&#1083;&#1102;
&#1055;&#1088;&#1072;&#1074;&#1086;&#1089;&#1083;&#1072;&#1074;i&#1103;.
&#1057;&#1074;&#1086;&#1076;&#1085;&#1099;&#1081;
&#1090;&#1077;&#1082;&#1089;&#1090;&#1098; &#1089;&#1098;
